- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper explores the trade-off between model size and performance, which is a common topic in machine learning. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with a popular deep learning architecture used in natural language processing. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper deals with neural network architectures. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the Transformer architecture has also been applied to computer vision tasks.
